\pard\sa80\f0\fs24 \b Conformance Checks\par
\pard\sa60\f0\fs18 \b 1. A record (first line)\b0  \u8212? present as the very first line of every file (FR manufacturer / serial, "ALXV\u8230?"). First character is "A" in all three.\par
\pard\sa60\f0\fs18 \b 2. Mandatory H-records\b0  \u8212? present in every file: HFDTE (flight date, DDMMYY), HFFXA (fix accuracy, 015), HFPLT (pilot), HFGTY (glider type), HFGID (glider ID / registration) and HFDTM (GNSS datum, 100 / WGS-1984). Competition logs also carry HFCID (competition number) and HFCCL (class).\par
\pard\sa60\f0\fs18 \b 3. B-records (fixes)\b0  \u8212? a full, untruncated set of GPS fixes is present in each file (15,462 \u8211? 29,839 fixes); none empty or cut mid-record.\par
\pard\sa60\f0\fs18 \b 4. Record order\b0  \u8212? records follow the spec order: A first, then H, I/J, C (task), then the time-series B/E/F/K block, with L (logbook) records permitted throughout.\par
\pard\sa60\f0\fs18 \b 5. Character set\b0  \u8212? every file is pure ASCII within the valid IGC set (upper-case A\u8211?Z, digits, space, - + . , : /). Lines use CRLF (carriage-return + line-feed) terminators as required by the spec; no accented or otherwise out-of-set characters appear in the data records.\par
\pard\sa200\f0\fs18 \b 6. Security (G) record\b0  \u8212? each file ends with a 5-line G (security) record block. The last B-record precedes the G block in every file, and \b zero\b0  data records (B/E/F/K) follow it \u8212? confirming the log is neither truncated, concatenated, nor tampered. Trailing L (logbook) records after the G block are permitted by the spec.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs24 \b Notes\par
\pard\sa120\f0\fs18 Header metadata matches the expected pilots and competition days: Antol\u237?n's log is dated 28-05-26 (18 Metre, TASK A \u8211? AAT), while Levin's and Kawa's logs are dated 29-05-26 (Open). All files were verified at download as genuine IGC content (Content-Type application/vnd.flight+igc).\par
